Reports a nested style rule whose syntax doesn't comply with the [PostCSS Nested](https://github.com/postcss/postcss-nested) or the [PostCSS Nesting](https://github.com/csstools/postcss-nesting) specification.

Example:


    .phone {
      &_title {}
    }

Reports a syntax error in a [PostCSS Custom Media](https://github.com/postcss/postcss-custom-media) query.

Example:


    @custom-media --small-viewport (max-width: 30em);

Reports a syntax error in [PostCSS Custom Selector](https://github.com/postcss/postcss-custom-selectors).

Example:


    @custom-selector :--heading h1, h2, h3;

Checks [range context](https://github.com/postcss/postcss-media-minmax) syntax, which may alternatively be used for media features with a 'range' type.

Example:


    @media screen and (500px <= width <= 1200px) {}

fullDescription.text:
Reports a multi-line selector. Most likely this means that several single-line selectors are actually intended but a comma is missing at the end of one or several lines. Example: 'input /* comma has probably been forgotten */
.button {
  margin: 1px;
}'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a multi-line selector. Most likely this means that several single-line selectors are actually intended but a comma is missing at the end of one or several lines.

**Example:**


    input /* comma has probably been forgotten */
    .button {
      margin: 1px;
    }

fullDescription.text:
Reports a duplicated CSS property within a ruleset. Respects shorthand properties. Example: '.foo {
  margin-bottom: 1px;
  margin-bottom: 1px; /* duplicates margin-bottom */
  margin: 0; /* overrides margin-bottom */
}'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a duplicated CSS property within a ruleset. Respects shorthand properties.

**Example:**


    .foo {
      margin-bottom: 1px;
      margin-bottom: 1px; /* duplicates margin-bottom */
      margin: 0; /* overrides margin-bottom */
    }

fullDescription.text:
Reports a CSS class reference in the 'composes' rule that cannot be resolved to any valid target. Example: '.className {/* ... */}

  .otherClassName {
    composes: className;
  }'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a CSS class reference in the ['composes'](https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules#composition) rule that cannot be resolved to any valid target.

**Example:**


      .className {/* ... */}

      .otherClassName {
        composes: className;
      }

fullDescription.text:
Reports inconsistencies between a YAML file and a JSON Schema if the schema is specified. Scheme example: '{
    "properties": {
      "SomeNumberProperty": {
        "type": "number"
      }
    }
  }' The following is an example with the corresponding warning: 'SomeNumberProperty: hello world'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports inconsistencies between a YAML file and a JSON Schema if the schema is specified.

**Scheme example:**


      {
        "properties": {
          "SomeNumberProperty": {
            "type": "number"
          }
        }
      }

**The following is an example with the corresponding warning:**


      SomeNumberProperty: hello world

fullDescription.text:
Reports deprecated keys in YAML files. Deprecation is checked only if there exists a JSON schema associated with the corresponding YAML file. Note that the deprecation mechanism is not defined in the JSON Schema specification yet, and this inspection uses a non-standard 'deprecationMessage' extension. Scheme deprecation example: '{
    "properties": {
      "SomeDeprecatedProperty": {
        "deprecationMessage": "Baz",
        "description": "Foo bar"
      }
    }
  }' The following is an example with the corresponding warning: 'SomeDeprecatedProperty: some value'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports deprecated keys in YAML files.

Deprecation is checked only if there exists a JSON schema associated with the corresponding YAML file.

Note that the deprecation mechanism is not defined in the JSON Schema specification yet,
and this inspection uses a non-standard `deprecationMessage` extension.

**Scheme deprecation example:**


      {
        "properties": {
          "SomeDeprecatedProperty": {
            "deprecationMessage": "Baz",
            "description": "Foo bar"
          }
        }
      }

**The following is an example with the corresponding warning:**


      SomeDeprecatedProperty: some value

fullDescription.text:
Reports a reference to a Less variable that is not resolved. Example: '* {
  margin: @unknown-var;
}'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a reference to a [Less variable](http://lesscss.org/features/#variables-feature) that is not resolved.

**Example:**


    * {
      margin: @unknown-var;
    }

fullDescription.text:
Reports a reference to a variable or mixin that is declared in another file, which is not explicitly imported in the current file. Example: '* {
  margin: @var-in-other-file;
}'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a reference to a variable or mixin that is declared in another file, which is not explicitly [imported](http://lesscss.org/features/#import-atrules-feature) in the current file.

**Example:**


    * {
      margin: @var-in-other-file;
    }

fullDescription.text:
Reports a reference to a Less mixin that is not resolved. Example: '* {
  .unknown-mixin();
}'

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a reference to a [Less mixin](http://lesscss.org/features/#mixins-feature) that is not resolved.

**Example:**


    * {
      .unknown-mixin();
    }

